        'The sweet spot is what some researchers call "desirable difficulty" — hard enough that you fail regularly, calibrated carefully enough that the failure is informative. You can feel the edge. The breakdown is specific. You can point to the exact moment where the system exceeded your capacity, which means you know exactly what to work on.',
        'This is not a fixed target. It moves as you develop.',
