        'Recovery structure in practice design refers to three related things.',
        'The first is the physical or procedural path back after failure. How do you reset? How quickly? Under what conditions? For a skater, this is the slope of the bowl — it gives you back your position, your orientation, your ability to try again. For a musician who makes an error in a passage, the recovery structure might be the decision rule: do you stop and restart the phrase, or do you continue and mark the error for focused work later? Do you reset to the beginning of the section or to three bars before the error? The decision rule is design. Choose it deliberately.',
