        'I\'ve used the phrase "productive failure" several times now. I want to be more specific about the distinction, because getting it wrong has consequences.',
        'Productive failure and demoralizing failure are not just failure with different emotional coloring. They\'re structurally different kinds of information, and they produce different developmental outcomes.',
        'Productive failure is specific, legible, and instructive. After a productive failure, you know more than you did before. You can point to where your capacity ran out — not in general, but at the specific moment, on the specific thing. You feel the edge. You understand the gap. The failure tells you exactly what to work on.',
