        'The person who has practiced in well-designed conditions for long enough doesn\'t just know more or perform better. They\'ve developed a different orientation to challenge itself. The edge of capacity is not a threatening place to them. It\'s where the interesting things happen. It\'s where they actually learn. The failure is not a judgment — it\'s information. The bowl is not a proving ground — it\'s a development engine.',
